 into \"ዲዛይነር\" (designer) and \"አሁን\" (now), similarly representing distinct noun and adverb.\nOther words with attached suffixes like 'ም', 'ን', 'ዋ', 'ዬ', 'አቸውን' were not split, as these are valid morphological inflections of the base word, not 'impossible morphological transitions' or merged independent words.\n\n**PROTOCOL 2: THE JUDGE (Nonsense Removal)**\nNo words were discarded as gibberish or unfixable OCR errors. All strings were either valid Amharic words, recognizable loanwords, or proper nouns.\n\n**PROTOCOL 3: THE CORRECTOR (Visual Repair)**\n- \"ዲዛይነ\" was corrected to \"ዲዛይነር\" (designer) as it appeared to be a truncated form of the common loanword.\n- \"ዲዛይሯ\" was interpreted and cleaned as \"ዲዛይነርዋ\" (her designer), recognizing a common Amharic contraction/spelling variation for clarity.\n\n**PROTOCOL 4: THE LEMMATIZER (Global Citation Form)**\nBase dictionary entries (roots) were identified for all words, including those with plural, possessive, or accusative suffixes. For many loanwords and proper nouns, the word itself serves as its own root.\n\n**PROTOCOL 5: THE TRANSLATOR (Nuance Expansion)**\nComprehensive English synonyms were provided for each word, aiming to capture their full meaning.\n\n**PROTOCOL 6: THE GRAMMARIAN (Linguistic Tagging)**\nPart of Speech (POS) tags were assigned based on the word's function in Amharic, including specific tags for proper nouns, acronyms, and gerunds.\n\n**PROTOCOL 7: THE FILTER (Size Constraint)**\nNo words or roots were discarded due to being single characters. All processed words and their roots were at least two characters long.\n\n**PROTOCOL 8: EXECUTIVE SUMMARY (Scholarly Guesses)**\n- The interpretation of \"ዲዛይሯ\" as \"ዲዛይነርዋ\" is a scholarly guess based on common Amharic orthographic practices where 'ነር' can be elided before 'ዋ' in informal or rapid writing, and the prevalence of 'ዲዛይነር' in other words in the batch.\n- The correction of \"ዲዛይነ\" to \"ዲዛይነር\" is a scholarly guess assuming an OCR error or truncation, given the high frequency of \"designer\" as a loanword.\n- Importance scores were assigned based on a general assessment of word frequency and cultural/scientific relevance within an Amharic context.","input_words":["ዲቦንም","ዲቪዛ","ዲቪያን","ዲቫክራን","ዲቬሎፕመንትን","ዲቴሪየም","ዲቴክቲንግ","ዲቶክሲፊኬሽን","ዲችኤቶ","ዲነራስ","ዲናም","ዲናንም","ዲናውያን","ዲንጋቲ","ዲኖበክሪ","ዲአርሶንሻ","ዲኤምቪ","ዲኦድራንቶችና","ዲኦፕተር","ዲውቲ","ዲዛኖች","ዲዛይሯ","ዲዛይነ","ዲዛይነርልብሶቿ","ዲዛይነርሰሞኑን","ዲዛይነርአሁን","ዲዛይነሮቼ","ዲዛይናቸውን","ዲዝኒን","ዲያመግነጢሳዊ"],"batch_number":null,"batch_label":null,"model_version":"gemini-2.5-flash"},{"id":"cccd9c55-8659-4cf5-aa8c-fe15a42bb99f","created_at":"2026-03-04T13:09:10.66192+00:00","word":null,"source_file":"rare_words_6.txt","batch_index":14130,"words":[{"pos":"Verb","root":"ማውደም","word":"እንዳያወድማት","synonyms":["to prevent from destroying her/it","so that he/she/it does not destroy her/it"],"importance":7},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ሰሞን","word":"ከሰሙኑ","synonyms":["from the recent week","recently","from the past few days"],"importance":6},{"pos":"Verb","root":"ማግለል","word":"ለማግላል","synonyms":["to isolate","to exclude","for the purpose of isolating"],"importance":7},{"pos":"Noun","root":"እምነት","word":"እምነት","synonyms":["faith","belief","trust","conviction"],"importance":8},{"pos":"Verb","root":"መዋሸት","word":"እንደማልዋሻቸው","synonyms":["that I will not lie to them"],"importance":7},{"pos":"Verb","root":"መዋሸት","word":"እንደማልዋሽላቸው","synonyms":["that I will not lie for them","that I will not lie on their behalf"],"importance":7},{"pos":"Adjective","root":"አንድ","word":"አንድ","synonyms":["one","a single"],"importance":6},{"pos":"Verb","root":"ማንሳት","word":"እናነሳ","synonyms":["we raise","we pick up","we lift"],"importance":6},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ነርቭ","word":"በነርቫችን","synonyms":["in our nerves","through our nerves"],"importance":6},{"pos":"Verb","root":"ማድረግ","word":"አረከኝ","synonyms":["he made me","he did to me"],"importance":7},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ኦሜሪ","word":"ኦሜሪ","synonyms":["Omari (a name)"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Ver